Subject: LM Studio Corpus Prompt Integration Disposition 015

Description: Diversified LM Studio worker prompt packet for integration disposition.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\LMStudioWorkerTaskCorpus.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_lmstudio_second_corpus_launch_queue\Derived_LMStudio_Second_Corpus_Launch_Queue_Source.sop

& [LMStudioCorpusPrompt:integration_disposition_015] is a non-mutating SOP worker prompt packet
  + [task_family] is integration_disposition
  + [prompt_boundary] is prompt-only, no tools, no file reads, no repo mutation, no hidden-state claims
  + [expected_output] is exactly one raw SOP node named InferenceJobResult with seven property lines and no Markdown
  + [validation_required_fields] is capture, validation, integration_disposition, evidence, outside, caution, next_step
  + [validation_required_terms] is integration_disposition, validation, evidence, outside
  + [validation_forbidden_terms] is self-integrated, file mutation, repo authority, hidden state access
  + [prompt_text] is:
    You are performing a no-tools SOP inference job from this prompt only.
    Do not call tools, inspect files, mutate state, or claim repo authority.
    Codex owns launch, capture, validation, integration, commits, and pushes.

    SOP primer:
    & [Name] is a subject declaration.
    + [field] is a property or inferred field.
    Integration disposition classifies a returned worker result without letting the worker integrate itself.

    Task family:
    integration_disposition tests whether you can hold captured output, validation, evidence, outside, caution, and next step apart.

    Returned result to classify:
    "A captured worker output has all required fields but one required literal term is missing."

    Return exactly these eight raw SOP lines and no extra text:
    & [InferenceJobResult] is integration disposition proposal
      + [capture] is ...
      + [validation] is ...
      + [integration_disposition] is ...
      + [evidence] is ...
      + [outside] is ...
      + [caution] is ...
      + [next_step] is ...

    Final check before answering:
    Line 1 must start with &.
    Lines 2 through 8 must use exactly this operator form: two spaces, +, space, [field], space, is, space, value.
    Do not replace is with verbs such as includes, separates, reminds, lists, or contains.
    Replace every ... placeholder with specific content; do not output ellipses or placeholder text.
    Use ASCII only; avoid curly quotes, nonbreaking hyphens, and special punctuation.
    Include the literal terms integration_disposition, validation, evidence, and outside at least once.
    Do not claim self-integrated, file mutation, repo authority, or hidden state access.
